Skype for Linux has moved from Alpha to Beta, and includes features which make the service easier to use. “We have been focused on building a new experience that is in line with Skype’s ongoing transition from peer-to-peer to a modern cloud architecture,” said the company. “We want to create a Linux version of Skype that is as feature rich as the existing Skype.” The Skype for Linux update includes performance improvements and many requests from the Linux community: